      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Code verification benchmarks relevant to contact mechanics and large-deformation elastoplasticity demonstrated. Required gradation 2: benchmark solutions compared to analytical or published reference solutions.",
      "rationale": "Hertzian contact and cantilever beam benchmarks executed in Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2. Results agree with analytical solutions to within 0.8%. Benchmark reports archived in project repository."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Systematic mesh convergence study with GCI < 2% for all QoIs. Required gradation 3: Richardson extrapolation across minimum three mesh densities with reported GCI.",
      "rationale": "Mesh convergence performed across coarse (2.1 mm), medium (1.05 mm), and fine (0.52 mm) element sizes at the screw-rod interface. Richardson extrapolation yields GCI of 1.1%, 0.9%, and 1.2% for stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm respectively. Medium mesh selected for production runs balancing accuracy and computational cost."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver convergence tolerances set to 1e-4 on force and displacement residuals. Required gradation 2: documented convergence criteria with residual monitoring.",
      "rationale": "Newton-Raphson iterations converge to force residual < 1e-4 and displacement residual < 1e-4 for all load steps. Convergence history archived for all 11 model runs. No divergence or excessive bisection observed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented simulation workflow with independent review of model setup. Required gradation 2: peer review of boundary conditions, material assignments, and loading protocol.",
      "rationale": "Model setup independently reviewed by a second engineer against the simulation plan (SIM-PLAN-COU1-v2). Boundary condition application, contact definitions, and material property assignments verified. No discrepancies identified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model (bilinear isotropic hardening) justified by material coupon data. Required gradation 3: model form selection supported by literature and coupon-level calibration.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V ELI bilinear isotropic hardening parameters (E=114 GPa, σ_y=880 MPa, E_t=2.2 GPa) derived from ASTM E8 tensile coupon tests on material from same lot as production screws. Literature comparison with Swanson et al. (2003) confirms model form adequacy for monotonic loading."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties from same material lot as test specimens; geometry from calibrated CMM measurements. Required gradation 3: inputs traceable to physical measurements with documented uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Geometry digitized via coordinate measuring machine (CMM) with calibration certificate traceable to NIST. Material properties from same Ti-6Al-4V ELI lot (heat number 4412-B). Friction coefficient (μ=0.2 at screw-rod interface) from literature (ASTM G99 pin-on-disk, stainless on titanium). Uncertainty in each input parameter documented in SIM-PLAN-COU1-v2 Table 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 test specimens from production-representative lot tested across two laboratories. Required gradation 3: specimens from production lot with documented dimensional inspection.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled from production-representative components (same drawing revision and material lot). Six constructs tested at Lab A (FDA/CDRH), five at Lab B (DePuy Synthes). Dimensional inspection records confirm screws within drawing tolerances."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of COU loading environments. Required gradation 3: multiple load levels or configurations tested. Achieved gradation 2: single test configuration (ASTM F1717 standard setup only).",
      "rationale": "ASTM F1717 static compression-bending conducted at a single load angle (5°) and single crosshead rate (5 mm/min) per the standard protocol. Only one test configuration was evaluated; dynamic or cyclic conditions were not included. This factor is below the required level and represents a known gap in the validation evidence base."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA model inputs demonstrably equivalent to test specimen properties and test machine boundary conditions. Required gradation 3: quantitative comparison of model inputs to measured specimen and test parameters.",
      "rationale": "CMM-measured screw geometry used directly in FEA geometry. Material properties from same lot. Test machine compliance measured and incorporated as spring elements in FEA boundary conditions. Rod pre-tension measured via strain gauge and matched in FEA. Quantitative input equivalency table provided in validation report Section 4.2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI differences <10% and E/uval < 1.96 for all primary QoIs. Required gradation 3: quantitative comparison metric with uncertainty normalization applied.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness: FEA 312 N/mm vs. experimental mean 308 N/mm (1.3% difference, E/uval=0.41). Yield force: FEA 1,847 N vs. experimental mean 1,823 N (1.3%, E/uval=0.38). Force at 40 mm: FEA 2,104 N vs. experimental mean 2,076 N (1.3%, E/uval=0.44). All acceptance criteria met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly linked to clinical failure modes and regulatory submission requirements. Required gradation 3: documented traceability from QoIs to device risk analysis and intended use.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and directly correspond to the pedicle screw construct's load-bearing performance requirements. Traceability to device FMEA (risk item R-04: screw fracture under compressive bending) documented in validation plan."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities replicate COU geometry, loading, and material conditions. Required gradation 3: validation scenario directly represents the COU with documented similarity argument.",
      "rationale": "Validation uses the identical 7.5 mm non-cannulated pedicle screw geometry, material lot, and ASTM F1717 test protocol as the COU. Similarity argument documented in validation plan Section 2.3: geometry is production-representative, loading is the regulatory standard test, and boundary conditions replicate the intended surgical implantation scenario (L4-L5 fixation with bilateral construct)."
    }
